    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Empty State</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">A centred message shown when a page, panel, or data surface has no content yet. It communicates the absence, explains the feature in one or two sentences, and offers a clear next action &#8212; with optional illustration, primary/secondary buttons, and a Supported platforms row.</p>
        <nav class="content-tabs">
          <button class="tab-item active">Overview</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Style</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Usage</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Code</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Accessibility</button>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

        <!-- ========== OVERVIEW ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-overview">
          <h3 id="anatomy" class="doc-h3">Anatomy</h3>
          <div class="anatomy-diagram">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;">
              <!-- Empty state preview with inline markers -->
              <div class="es-container" style="padding:24px 20px;margin:0;">
                <div style="position:relative;">
                  <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;right:calc(100% + 6px);transform:translateY(-50%);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;z-index:5;"><span class="anat-marker-inline">1</span><div style="width:28px;height:2px;background:#2563eb;"></div></div>
                  <div class="es-illustration" style="width:140px;height:140px;margin-bottom:16px;">
                    <img src="assets/Illustration/network-device-group.svg" alt="">
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div style="position:relative;">
                  <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;right:calc(100% + 6px);transform:translateY(-50%);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;z-index:5;"><span class="anat-marker-inline">2</span><div style="width:28px;height:2px;background:#2563eb;"></div></div>
                  <div class="es-title">Explore a diverse array of configurations</div>
                </div>
                <div style="position:relative;">
                  <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;right:calc(100% + 6px);transform:translateY(-50%);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;z-index:5;"><span class="anat-marker-inline">3</span><div style="width:28px;height:2px;background:#2563eb;"></div></div>
                  <div class="es-description">Configurations helps you manage applications, system settings, and security policies across your network. <a href="#">Learn more</a></div>
                </div>
                <div style="position:relative;">
                  <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;right:calc(100% + 6px);transform:translateY(-50%);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;z-index:5;"><span class="anat-marker-inline">4</span><div style="width:28px;height:2px;background:#2563eb;"></div></div>
                  <div class="es-actions" style="margin-bottom:0;position:relative;">
                    <button class="es-btn primary">Create configuration</button>
                    <button class="es-btn secondary">Learn more</button>
                    <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;left:calc(100% + 6px);transform:translateY(-50%);display:flex;flex-direction:row-reverse;align-items:center;gap:6px;z-index:5;"><span class="anat-marker-inline">5</span><div style="width:28px;height:2px;background:#2563eb;"></div></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="es-supported" style="position:relative;">
                  <div style="position:absolute;top:50%;right:calc(100% + 6px);transform:translateY(-50%);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;z-index:5;"><span class="anat-marker-inline">6</span><div style="width:28px;height:2px;background:#2563eb;"></div></div>
                  <span class="es-supported-label">Supported</span>
                  <div class="es-supported-icons" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);">
                    Windows &#8226; macOS &#8226; Linux
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="anat-legend" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);">
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">1</span><div><strong>Illustration</strong><span>Centred decorative spot illustration (~200 &times; 160 px) that communicates the feature theme. Swappable via the instance-swap slot.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">2</span><div><strong>Title</strong><span>Primary headline &#8212; one sentence, action-oriented. Semibold 16 px, Text-Primary.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">3</span><div><strong>Description</strong><span>Supporting paragraph, 1&#8211;2 sentences. 14 px, Text-Secondary. May contain an inline "Learn more" link.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">4</span><div><strong>Primary Action</strong><span>Solid brand button &#8212; the single most useful next step. Toggleable via Show Primary Action.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">5</span><div><strong>Secondary Action</strong><span>Subtle/ghost button for alternatives (Learn more, View docs). Toggleable via Show Secondary Action.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">6</span><div><strong>Supported Row</strong><span>"Supported" label + up to 3 OS / platform icons. Show only when compatibility materially affects the action.</span></div></div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div style="margin-bottom:64px;">
            <h2 id="live-demo" class="doc-section-title" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Preview</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle" style="margin-bottom:28px;">Empty states across common scenarios &#8212; no devices, access denied, nothing scheduled, and no uploads.</p>
            <div class="demo-container">
<div class="demo-canvas">
                <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(320px,1fr));gap:24px;">
                  <!-- No devices -->
                  <div class="es-demo-wrap">
                    <div class="es-container">
                      <div class="es-illustration"><img src="assets/Illustration/network-device-group.svg" alt=""></div>
                      <div class="es-title">No devices enrolled</div>
                      <div class="es-description">Enrol your first device to start managing configurations, policies, and patches across your network. <a href="#">Learn more</a></div>
                      <div class="es-actions">
                        <button class="es-btn primary">Enrol device</button>
                        <button class="es-btn secondary">View docs</button>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <!-- Access denied -->
                  <div class="es-demo-wrap">
                    <div class="es-container">
                      <div class="es-illustration"><img src="assets/Illustration/access-denied.svg" alt=""></div>
                      <div class="es-title">You don&rsquo;t have access</div>
                      <div class="es-description">This workspace is restricted. Contact an administrator to request access to configurations and security policies.</div>
                      <div class="es-actions">
                        <button class="es-btn primary">Request access</button>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <!-- Nothing scheduled -->
                  <div class="es-demo-wrap">
                    <div class="es-container">
                      <div class="es-illustration"><img src="assets/Illustration/schedule-task.svg" alt=""></div>
                      <div class="es-title">Nothing scheduled</div>
                      <div class="es-description">Create a scheduled task to automate patch jobs, reports, and policy rollouts across endpoints.</div>
                      <div class="es-actions">
                        <button class="es-btn primary">Schedule a task</button>
                        <button class="es-btn secondary">Browse templates</button>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <!-- No uploads -->
                  <div class="es-demo-wrap">
                    <div class="es-container">
                      <div class="es-illustration"><img src="assets/Illustration/upload-cloud.svg" alt=""></div>
                      <div class="es-title">No files uploaded yet</div>
                      <div class="es-description">Drag and drop files here, or click upload to share assets with your team.</div>
                      <div class="es-actions">
                        <button class="es-btn primary">Upload file</button>
                      </div>
                      <div class="es-supported">
                        <span class="es-supported-label">Supported</span>
                        <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);">PDF, PNG, JPG, CSV &#8226; up to 25 MB</span>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Write a specific, feature-named title ("Start your first patch job").</li>
                <li>Pair the empty state with at least one clear next action.</li>
                <li>Use an illustration that matches the feature theme.</li>
                <li>Keep description to &le; 2 lines at the default size.</li>
                <li>Use the primary-button style for the <strong>one</strong> expected next action.</li>
                <li>Centre-align the block in its container.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Write generic titles ("No data", "Nothing here") &#8212; wastes the opportunity.</li>
                <li>Show an empty state with no clear next step.</li>
                <li>Use a generic mascot for unrelated features.</li>
                <li>Write a paragraph of marketing copy in the description.</li>
                <li>Stack multiple solid primary buttons &#8212; users cannot tell which to click.</li>
                <li>Left-align the block in a wide container &#8212; it reads as an error.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ========== STYLE ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-style" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <h2 id="style-overview" class="doc-section-title">Style</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Layout variants, design tokens, and spacing that define the Empty State&rsquo;s appearance.</p>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="layout-variants" class="doc-section-title">Layout Variants</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Three layout patterns cover the most common empty-state contexts &#8212; default panel, compact drawer, and full-page with Supported row.</p>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(300px,1fr));gap:20px;margin-top:24px;">
              <!-- Default -->
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:14px;">
                <div style="display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:center;padding:20px;background:var(--prism-black);border-radius:10px;margin-bottom:16px;min-height:240px;">
                  <div class="es-container" style="padding:16px;max-width:260px;">
                    <div class="es-illustration" style="width:100px;height:100px;margin-bottom:12px;"><img src="assets/Illustration/network-device-group.svg" alt=""></div>
                    <div class="es-title" style="font-size:14px;">No devices found</div>
                    <div class="es-description" style="font-size:12px;margin-bottom:12px;">Enrol your first device.</div>
                    <div class="es-actions"><button class="es-btn primary" style="padding:6px 14px;font-size:12px;">Enrol device</button></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div style="font-size:14.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);">Default</div>
                <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;">Illustration + title + description + primary action. Best for panels and lists.</div>
              </div>
              <!-- Compact -->
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:14px;">
                <div style="display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:center;padding:20px;background:var(--prism-black);border-radius:10px;margin-bottom:16px;min-height:240px;">
                  <div class="es-container compact" style="padding:12px;max-width:240px;">
                    <div class="es-illustration" style="width:72px;height:72px;margin-bottom:8px;"><img src="assets/Illustration/access-denied.svg" alt=""></div>
                    <div class="es-title" style="font-size:13px;">No access</div>
                    <div class="es-description" style="font-size:11px;margin-bottom:10px;">Contact admin.</div>
                    <div class="es-actions"><button class="es-btn primary" style="padding:5px 12px;font-size:11px;">Request</button></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div style="font-size:14.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);">Compact</div>
                <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;">Smaller illustration + condensed type. Best for drawers, cards, and small panels.</div>
              </div>
              <!-- With Supported Row -->
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:14px;">
                <div style="display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:center;padding:20px;background:var(--prism-black);border-radius:10px;margin-bottom:16px;min-height:240px;">
                  <div class="es-container" style="padding:16px;max-width:280px;">
                    <div class="es-illustration" style="width:90px;height:90px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="assets/Illustration/two-factor-auth.svg" alt=""></div>
                    <div class="es-title" style="font-size:13px;">Set up 2FA</div>
                    <div class="es-description" style="font-size:11px;margin-bottom:10px;">Protect your account.</div>
                    <div class="es-actions"><button class="es-btn primary" style="padding:5px 12px;font-size:11px;">Enable</button></div>
                    <div class="es-supported" style="margin-top:14px;padding-top:10px;">
                      <span class="es-supported-label" style="font-size:10px;">Supported</span>
                      <span style="font-size:10px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);">Windows &#8226; macOS &#8226; Linux</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div style="font-size:14.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);">With Supported Row</div>
                <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;">Adds platform/OS icons below the action cluster. Use for agent-installs and OS-targeted policies.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="color-tokens" class="doc-h3">Color Tokens<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Tokens</span></h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Token</th><th>Applied to</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Surface</td><td><code>Background/BG-Primary-alt</code></td><td>Page or panel background behind the empty state</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Title</td><td><code>Text/Text-Primary</code></td><td>Primary headline</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Description</td><td><code>Text/Text-Secondary</code></td><td>Supporting paragraph</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Inline link</td><td><code>Text/Text-Link</code></td><td>"Learn more" link inside description</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Supported label</td><td><code>Text/Text-Tertiary</code></td><td>"Supported" label in the OS row</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Platform glyphs</td><td><code>Border/Icon/Icon-Tertiary</code></td><td>OS / platform icons</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Primary button</td><td><code>Background/BG-Brand-Solid</code> + <code>Text/Text-Inverse</code></td><td>Inherits Button primary tokens</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Secondary button</td><td>Inherits Button subtle variant</td><td>Outline / ghost style</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="spacing-tokens" class="doc-h3">Spacing Tokens</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Value</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>spacing/8</code></td><td>8 px</td><td>Title &harr; description gap; between supported label and icons</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>spacing/12</code></td><td>12 px</td><td>Primary &harr; secondary button gap; between OS icons</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>spacing/16</code></td><td>16 px</td><td>Description &harr; action row gap; action &harr; supported row gap</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>spacing/24</code></td><td>24 px</td><td>Illustration &harr; title gap</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="sizing-reference" class="doc-h3">Sizing Reference</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Illustration size (md)</td><td>~200 &times; 160 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Illustration size (sm)</td><td>~120 &times; 96 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Illustration size (lg)</td><td>~280 &times; 220 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Max text width</td><td><strong>480 px</strong> (keeps description to ~2 lines at md)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>OS icon size</td><td>16 &times; 16 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Container horizontal padding</td><td>24 px (inherits panel padding)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Horizontal alignment</td><td>Centred</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="typography" class="doc-h3">Typography</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">All Empty State text uses <strong>Zoho Puvi</strong>. Title is Semibold, description and buttons are Regular / Medium.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Element</th><th>Size</th><th>Weight</th><th>Line Height</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Title</td><td>16 px</td><td><code>600 (Semibold)</code></td><td>24 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Description</td><td>14 px</td><td><code>400 (Regular)</code></td><td>20 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Inline link</td><td>14 px</td><td><code>500 (Medium)</code></td><td>20 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Primary / Secondary button label</td><td>14 px</td><td><code>500 (Medium)</code></td><td>20 px</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Supported label</td><td>13 px</td><td><code>400 (Regular)</code></td><td>20 px</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="border-radius" class="doc-h3">Border Radius</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Value</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>border-radius/radius-6</code></td><td>6 px</td><td>Button corners (inherited from Button)</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ========== USAGE ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Empty State is designed for zero-content surfaces &#8212; first-time lists, empty search results, gated views, and disabled features.</p>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px;">
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>When to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">A list, table, or grid has no items yet for a first-time user ("no configurations yet").</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">A search / filter result is empty ("no matches for &lsquo;xyz&rsquo;").</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">A feature is available but not yet activated ("enable single sign-on to continue").</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">A permission-gated view has nothing to show for the current role.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>When NOT to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Loading</strong> &#8212; use a skeleton or spinner, not an empty state.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Error</strong> &#8212; use Inline Alert Message or a dedicated error state.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Success confirmation</strong> after an action &#8212; use a Toast.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;"><strong>First-run tutorials</strong> &#8212; use an onboarding flow, not an empty state.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:16px 20px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.15);border-radius:12px;">
              <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Always pair an empty state with <strong>at least one path forward</strong> &#8212; create something, adjust filters, request access, or read more.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="illustration-selection" class="doc-section-title">Illustration Selection</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Pick an illustration whose subject matches the feature domain. Generic mascots dilute meaning &#8212; use domain-specific spot illustrations.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Recommended Illustration</th><th>Asset</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>No devices / no endpoints</td><td>Network device group</td><td><code>network-device-group.svg</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Permission denied / restricted view</td><td>Access denied</td><td><code>access-denied.svg</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Nothing scheduled</td><td>Schedule / task</td><td><code>schedule-task.svg</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Authentication / 2FA</td><td>Two-factor auth</td><td><code>two-factor-auth.svg</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>No uploads / empty drop zone</td><td>Upload cloud</td><td><code>upload-cloud.svg</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>No search results</td><td>Common search / file search</td><td><code>common-search.svg</code></td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="message-tone" class="doc-section-title">Message Tone</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Write clear, specific copy that invites action. Avoid passive phrasing and marketing fluff.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Element</th><th>Guidance</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>Title</strong></td><td>One sentence, &le; 50 characters. Action-oriented ("Start your first automation") or descriptive ("No configurations yet"). Avoid "There are no&hellip;".</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Description</strong></td><td>1&#8211;2 sentences that explain <em>what the feature does</em> and <em>why the user should act</em>. End with a "Learn more" link when documentation exists.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Primary action</strong></td><td>The single most useful next step. Prefer a verb phrase &#8212; "Create configuration", "Invite teammate" &#8212; not "OK".</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Secondary action</strong></td><td>Optional lower-commitment alternative &#8212; "Learn more", "View docs", "Import". Omit when there&rsquo;s nothing useful to offer.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Supported row</strong></td><td>Include only when platform compatibility materially affects the action (agent install, OS-targeted policy). Omit for generic empty states.</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do&rsquo;s and Don&rsquo;ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for crafting effective empty states that drive user action.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Write a specific title:</strong> "Start your first patch job" &#8212; feature-named, action-oriented.</li>
                <li><strong>Pair with an action:</strong> Every empty state must expose at least one clear next step.</li>
                <li><strong>Match illustration to feature:</strong> Use the domain-relevant spot illustration.</li>
                <li><strong>Keep description short:</strong> 1&#8211;2 lines max at default size.</li>
                <li><strong>Use one primary button:</strong> The one thing users should do next.</li>
                <li><strong>Centre the block:</strong> Keeps the page feeling intentional, not broken.</li>
                <li><strong>Hide Supported row when irrelevant:</strong> Only show OS icons for OS-specific actions.</li>
                <li><strong>Localise the Supported row:</strong> Translate OS names in Arabic/Hebrew/CJK layouts.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Generic titles:</strong> "No data", "Nothing here" &#8212; these waste the opportunity.</li>
                <li><strong>No action:</strong> Empty states without a next step leave users stuck.</li>
                <li><strong>Generic mascots:</strong> A cute character unrelated to the feature is noise.</li>
                <li><strong>Marketing paragraph:</strong> Avoid long, brochure-style descriptions.</li>
                <li><strong>Multiple primary buttons:</strong> Users cannot tell which is "the" action.</li>
                <li><strong>Left-align in wide container:</strong> Reads as an error, not an empty state.</li>
                <li><strong>Forced platform icons:</strong> Don&rsquo;t show Windows/macOS/Linux on OS-agnostic features.</li>
                <li><strong>Unlocalised OS names:</strong> Don&rsquo;t leave OS labels un-translated in RTL/CJK.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="related" class="doc-section-title">Related</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or are often used alongside Empty State.</p>
            <div class="related-grid">
              <a href="Inline-message.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4M12 16h.01"/></svg> Inline Alert Message</a>
              <a href="Snackbar.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="8" width="18" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M3 12h18"/></svg> Toast</a>
              <a href="Data-table.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M3 15h18M9 3v18"/></svg> Data Table</a>
              <a href="Button.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="8" width="18" height="8" rx="4"/></svg> Button</a>
              <a href="Illustrations.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 15.75l5.159-5.159a2.25 2.25 0 013.182 0l5.159 5.159m-1.5-1.5l1.409-1.409a2.25 2.25 0 013.182 0l2.909 2.909"/></svg> Illustrations</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="references" class="doc-section-title">References</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens and resources for implementing the Empty State component.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">10208:202426</code> &#8212; Component Set: Empty State</li>
              <li><strong>Figma Source:</strong> <a href="https://www.figma.com/design/DahIgbIJrSkzyP3OoHaDaG/UEMS---Design-System-3.0?node-id=10208-202426" target="_blank" style="color:var(--prism-violet);font-weight:600;">UEMS Design System 3.0 &#8212; Empty State</a></li>
              <li><strong>Typography:</strong> Zoho Puvi Semibold (600) for title, Regular (400) for description, Medium (500) for buttons and links</li>
              <li><strong>Max text width:</strong> 480 px &#8212; keeps description to ~2 lines at default size</li>
              <li><strong>Illustrations:</strong> Sourced from <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">assets/Illustration/</code> &#8212; 50 SVG spot illustrations</li>
            </ul>
